---
<BaseLayout title="Grusha G S — AI Product Strategist">
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-greeting">
        <span>ನಮಸ್ಕಾರ</span>
        <span>नमस्ते</span>
        <span>வணக்கம்</span>
        <span>Hello</span>
        <span>নমস্কার</span>
        <span>నమస్కారం</span>
        <span>നമസ്കാരം</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-name">Grusha<br/>G S</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        I build AI products that work in the languages most of India actually speaks. Currently shipping multilingual voice systems at Shunya Labs.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-status">Open to product roles</div>
      <div class="hero-links">
        <a href="mailto:grushags90@gmail.com">Email</a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/grusha-gs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/Grusha15" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://huggingface.co/grushaaaaa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hugging Face</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="section-label">Selected Work</div>
      <ul class="work-list">
        <li class="work-item">
          <a href="/case-studies/bas-itna-paradox">
            <h3 class="work-item-title">Kirana Grammar vs. Instamart Logic</h3>
            <p class="work-item-description">
              Why Swiggy Instamart is losing the daily Indian household, and what it would take to win it back. A product case study on catalog architecture, user agency, and the gap between how quick commerce thinks and how Indian households actually shop.
            </p>
            <div class="work-item-meta">
              <span>Case Study</span>
              <span>2026</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>

        <li class="work-item">
          <a href="https://shunyalabs.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <h3 class="work-item-title">Vak — Indic Real-Time Translation</h3>
            <p class="work-item-description">
              Real-time translation across 55 Indic languages and 2,970 translation pairs, launched at the India-AI Impact Summit 2026. One of the most expansive multilingual deployments in the Indian AI ecosystem. Core contributor.
            </p>
            <div class="work-item-meta">
              <span>Production AI</span>
              <span>Shunya Labs</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about">
      <div class="section-label">About</div>
      <p>
        I am a data scientist by training and an AI product strategist by practice. I work at Shunya Labs on multilingual voice and language systems for the Indian market — fine-tuning ASR models to under 10% word error rate at sub-second latency, designing synthetic data pipelines for low-resource languages, and translating enterprise constraints into deployable AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before Shunya, I co-authored Nasscom's national AI research blueprint, which identified twenty high-impact AI research domains and shaped India's research agenda. I have a paper under review at ICML 2026 and another at Interspeech.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am writing case studies like the one above because I want to formalize the product thinking I have been doing informally for the last two years. The next role I am looking for is one where I can do that thinking with a title and a team that matches it.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>